  "character_tips": {
    "anna": "These are real sentences now, not drills. Feel how the rhythm carries you from one word to the next. - Eleanor Hayes, editor",
    "maxim": "Let your eyes run a word or two ahead of your hands. The fingers do their best work when they already know what is coming. - Eleanor Hayes, editor",
    "knopych": "Words joined into sentences. That is the whole trade in miniature. Keep the line moving. - Eleanor Hayes, editor",
    "klavochka": "You are putting words together into something whole. That is writing, plainly. Stay with the rhythm. - Eleanor Hayes, editor"
